Eto’o May Become Top-Paid Player in Move to Russia, Associated Press Says

-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 
2011-08-21T19:40:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-21/eto-o-may-become-top-paid-player-in-move-to-russia-associated-press-says.html
Inter Milan reached a deal to
transfer Samuel Eto’o to  Russia ’s Anzhi Makhachkala in a
transaction that could see the striker becoming the world’s
highest-paid soccer player, the  Associated Press  reported,
citing Italian media.  The AP said the clubs agreed on a transfer fee of $38.9
million, with Cameroon’s Eto’o getting a three-year contract
worth $28.8 million a season, based on Italian reports.  The deal may be formalized tomorrow after several days of
talks, the AP added.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter-Joseph Hegarty at 
 phegarty@bloomberg.net  